a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re (-4)) (Im (7/6))"
shows  "cmod a = 25/6"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\left|{-4+\frac{7}{6}i}\right|$. The final Answer is \frac{25}{6}
 ### Proof
 We have $\left|{-4+\frac{7}{6}i}\right|=\frac{1}{6}|{-24+7i}|=\frac{1}{6}\sqrt{(-24)^2+7^2}=\boxed{\frac{25}{6}}$
 *)

theorem
fixes a :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re (-4)) (Im (7/6))"
shows  "cmod a = 25/6"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Calculate the magnitude of the complex number $-4 + \frac{7}{6}i$. The final answer is $\frac{25}{6}$.
